  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      vitamin C or ascorbic acid has known role in tissue repair. due to it's
      properties(water_soluble), vitamin c is not stored in the body and when depleted, the
      bleeding tendency will increase due to dysfunctional connective tissues production in vessel
      wall and it has some important functions in platelets.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      In this randomized clinical trial, 1000 mg vitamin C will administrate intravenously a day
      before surgery and during surgery in patients who undergo abdominal hysterectomy.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
